<font color="#FF0000">DON'T FORGET!</font><br>
<tt>Mon May 26  7:42:57 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
As we remember our fallen comrades, let us also remember the mistakes, and the people who made them, and why those mistakes were made.  Let us vow to truly support freedom for all people.  Let us be willing to listen to other voices, other views.  As great as this country is, it is not perfect.  Our brothers and sisters who died in Vietnam died in a needless war, a war that could and should have been avoided.  Regardless of the reasons for our intervention there, we have a Wall with 58,000 names on it that should never have been built (I love the Wall, I hate the reason for it's existence).
